                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word God is rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works</desc>
                  <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#121v #122r" facs="122">fols. 121v, 122r</locus> (tenth biblical canticle)</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                  <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#1r #7r #21r #30r #37v #43r #51v #70r #75v #87v #99r #102r #113v #133r" facs="001 007 021 030 038 043 052 070 076 088 099 102 114 133">folss. 1r, 7r, 21r, 30r, 37v, 43r, 51v, 70r, 75v, 87v, 99r, 102r, 113v, 133r, </locus> (ḥaräg);
                    <locus target="#1r" facs="001">1r, </locus> (line of alternating red and black dots);
                    <locus target="#13v #62r #107v #125v #149r" facs="014 062 108 126 149">13v, 62r, 107v, 125v, 149r, </locus> (multiple full stops between lines of alternating red and black dots);
                    <locus target="#75r" facs="075">75r</locus> (line of black dots)
                  </decoNote>
                </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#57r" facs="057">Fol. 57r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    the midpoint of the psalms is marked with the crude drawing of a bird
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#2r #9r #27r #32r" facs="002 009 027 032">Fols. 2r, 9r, 27r, 32r</locus>
                    <desc>etc., words of text are written interlinearly
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <locus target="#2v #4r #43v #69r #97v" facs="003 004 044 069 098">Fols. 2v, 4r, 43v, 69r, 97v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    lines of text are written interlinearly
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <locus target="#127v" facs="128">f. 127v, line 1</locus>
                    <desc>
                    lines of text are written in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <locus target="#137v #138r" facs="138">Fols. 137v, 138r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    erasure markings are visible
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <locus target="#38r #48r #66v #136v #137r" facs="038 048 067 137">Fols. 38r, 48r, 66v, 136v, 137r</locus>
                    <desc>etc., text has been removed
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <desc>
                    The scribe’s chosen aspect ratio for the codex combined with the script size forces the scribe to complete the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
                <bindingDesc>
                  <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
                    <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment, four Coptic chain stitches attached with bridle attachments to rough-hewn boards of the traditional wood, covered with tooled leather, headband and tailband.</decoNote>
                    <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                      <material key="parchment"/>
                      <material key="wood"/>
                      <material key="leather"/>
                    </decoNote>
                  </binding>
                </bindingDesc>
